<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1806-06-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1806-06-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="89" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                        <head><seg type="margin">[634]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Miranda</persName> to Admiral <persName type="to">Cochrane</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Barbadoes</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1806-06-09"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 9,
                                1806</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Having deliberately perused the foregoing
                            proposals, I hereby bind and oblige myself, as far as my authority can
                            extend, to see the same carried into execution; and that, to all intents
                            and purposes, the same shall be ratified and made binding on those
                            provinces that may become independent of Spain.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your most obedient, humble servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>F. DE MIRANDA.</signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Rear-Admiral the Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">A. Cochrane</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Commander-in-Chief, &amp;c., &amp;c.,
                                    Barbadoes.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>